      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Quality mare JILLIBY BALLERINI (7) looks a class above these. Comes off a second to Keayang Zahara in the Group 1 Hammerhead Mile in Sydney, the third time she has chased her star stalemate home this campaign. Kicked off the preparation with four straight wins including the Kilmore and Bendigo cups and the drop to this level should see her back in the winners' list. IMPERIAL MONARCH NZ (6) did a good job for fourth to Keayang Zahara in the Grand Prix two back before delivering a strong win by more than 10m in the Geelong Cup last time. Goes back 10m in the handicap off that win but he is two from two at this venue. EL RESAMO (5) switches from mobile start racing but is in good form, coming from a wide barrier for a 1.5m third at Melton two back before winning at that circuit last week. MEADOW VALLEY STAR (4) has been racing consistently in SA and while this stronger he can be competitive from the front mark.",
